CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 11, 1962, pg. 6 reads: " "Tadpoles" - Each year the Pittsburgh Frogs give a series of events, one of them being a teen-age dancing party. Shown here are "Tadpoles," youngsters of Frogs' members.  Last Monday night they had a real ball at the dance, held at Loendi Club.  Only adult present on the picture is Percy Garland (second from right), chairman of the party committee.  This is the 52nd year of the celebrations of the exclusive men's group. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of young women and men, including Veronica Rickmond and Stephanie Sawyer in front, and Mr. Waddy in back, gathered around table with ice bucket and chafing dishes, in Loendi Club for FROGS "Tadpole" teenage dance party
